until it dries, Sid.


366
00:38:46.214 --> 00:38:47.694
I'll be an old man by then.

367
00:38:47.737 --> 00:38:51.567
Come on,
we're just gonna have to do it again.


368
00:38:51.611 --> 00:38:55.310
Nope, I've almost got it...

369
00:39:03.449 --> 00:39:05.059
Damn it!

370
00:39:05.103 --> 00:39:06.147
I'm sorry, Alex.

371
00:39:06.191 --> 00:39:07.540
"I'm sorry, Alex"?

372
00:39:07.583 --> 00:39:10.586
How about listening
to me for once?


373
00:40:03.900 --> 00:40:06.686
Feels good, doesn't it?

374
00:40:07.991 --> 00:40:10.472
I have to get
Sandy to the doctor.


375
00:40:10.516 --> 00:40:12.082
You two gonna be...

376
00:40:12.126 --> 00:40:13.214
Oh, honey, that's great!

377
00:40:13.258 --> 00:40:17.566
Is Louis turning you
into a clown?


378
00:40:18.567 --> 00:40:20.917
Will you be staying for dinner?

379
00:40:20.961 --> 00:40:22.005
Probably not.

380
00:40:22.049 --> 00:40:23.050
Mommy...

381
00:40:23.093 --> 00:40:23.964
It's OK, sweetheart.

382
00:40:24.007 --> 00:40:26.096
I'll be back in a little while.

383
00:40:26.140 --> 00:40:30.100
You remember your bedtime, OK?

384
00:40:51.426 --> 00:40:52.906
Alex?

385
00:40:52.949 --> 00:40:55.735
Can I come in?

386
00:41:11.098 --> 00:41:14.710
It's quite a look for you.

387
00:41:20.542 --> 00:41:22.892
Bad day?

388
00:41:24.503 --> 00:41:25.721
I've had better.

389
00:41:25.765 --> 00:41:27.375
Apparently.

390
00:41:27.419 --> 00:41:29.551
I've been seeing things.

391
00:41:29.595 --> 00:41:30.552
Have you?

392
00:41:30.596 --> 00:41:32.554
Things that can't be real.

393
00:41:32.598 --> 00:41:34.556
What?

394
00:41:34.991 --> 00:41:37.951
I thought I saw Louis.

395
00:41:37.994 --> 00:41:39.648
Really?

396
00:41:39.692 --> 00:41:43.478
Was he riding the
Loch Ness monster?


397
00:41:43.522 --> 00:41:45.437
Sandra, it's not funny.

398
00:41:45.480 --> 00:41:47.526
No, it's not funny.

399
00:41:47.569 --> 00:41:50.572
It's not funny at all.

400
00:41:52.052 --> 00:41:55.011
Al, this place
isn't right for us.


401
00:41:55.055 --> 00:41:56.404
I can handle it.

402
00:41:56.448 --> 00:41:59.320
Can you?
And how come you look like this?


403
00:41:59.364 --> 00:42:01.322
And how come every
time I turn around


404
00:42:01.366 --> 00:42:02.802
something else is broken?

405
00:42:02.845 --> 00:42:03.977
I'm getting it together.

406
00:42:04.020 --> 00:42:05.580
Why is it that every
time someone offers


407
00:42:05.605 --> 00:42:06.588
to buy this shithole,

408
00:42:06.632 --> 00:42:08.286
it's not good enough for you?

409
00:42:08.329 --> 00:42:09.591
Not good enough for us.

410
00:42:09.635 --> 00:42:10.505
Fuck that!

411
00:42:10.549 --> 00:42:11.941
Why don't you just admit to me

412
00:42:11.985 --> 00:42:14.379
that you don't really want
to sell this place at all?


413
00:42:14.422 --> 00:42:17.164
Because I don't.

414
00:42:18.034 --> 00:42:21.386
This is mom's place.

415
00:42:26.478 --> 00:42:30.220
I know it's not much.

416
00:42:31.309 --> 00:42:34.573
But it's all that
we have left of her.


417
00:42:36.575 --> 00:42:39.491
If we let it go...

418
00:42:41.623 --> 00:42:45.366
Our memories of her
will go with it.


419
00:42:52.460 --> 00:42:55.985
I have a present for you.

420
00:42:59.902 --> 00:43:03.776
I was saving this
for your birthday.


421
00:43:09.695 --> 00:43:14.482
Remember how scared you
were to ride the Ferris wheel?


422
00:43:14.526 --> 00:43:15.527
Yeah.

423
00:43:15.570 --> 00:43:17.964
Till mom told me
it was like jumping,


424
00:43:18.007 --> 00:43:21.881
except you never really fall.

425
