I felt that it
just couldn't wait.


546
00:57:21.850 --> 00:57:23.504
What's going on?

547
00:57:24.201 --> 00:57:29.336
Well, I've been having the... You know,
the stress thing.


548
00:57:29.380 --> 00:57:31.512
Like right after the accident.

549
00:57:31.556 --> 00:57:33.210
Car accident?

550
00:57:33.253 --> 00:57:35.124
Yes.

551
00:57:36.300 --> 00:57:41.392
I've been telling myself
that everything's... Fine


552
00:57:41.435 --> 00:57:43.394
and that I'm OK.

553
00:57:45.396 --> 00:57:48.312
Everything's not fine,

554
00:57:48.355 --> 00:57:50.096
and I'm not OK.

555
00:57:50.139 --> 00:57:51.837
What seems to be the problem?

556
00:57:51.880 --> 00:57:54.883
I've been seeing things.

557
00:57:54.927 --> 00:57:57.408
What is it that
you've been seeing?


558
00:57:57.451 --> 00:57:59.410
Louis.

559
00:58:00.715 --> 00:58:02.630
I've been seeing Louis.

560
00:58:02.674 --> 00:58:03.805
And...

561
00:58:03.849 --> 00:58:06.591
Have you tried talking
to him about that?


562
00:58:07.592 --> 00:58:08.854
He's dead.

563
00:58:08.897 --> 00:58:10.508
I see.

564
00:58:10.551 --> 00:58:14.338
Don't you remember?
You counseled me right after the accident.


565
00:58:14.381 --> 00:58:16.427
You said...

566
00:58:17.993 --> 00:58:22.128
Look, I think I need
some help here.


567
00:58:22.781 --> 00:58:27.612
Alex, I will try
my best to help you.


568
00:58:30.876 --> 00:58:32.791
Can I smoke in here?

569
00:58:32.834 --> 00:58:34.836
Of course.

570
00:58:37.622 --> 00:58:41.930
How long ago did this
accident take place?


571
00:58:42.975 --> 00:58:44.455
5 months ago.

572
00:58:44.498 --> 00:58:48.285
Are you telling me that you
can't remember back 5 months?


573
00:58:48.328 --> 00:58:49.851
Yes, we keep excellent records,

574
00:58:49.895 --> 00:58:54.552
and I like to think I keep
very good track of my patients.


575
00:58:55.814 --> 00:58:57.511
Good, you can pull my file,

576
00:58:57.555 --> 00:59:01.472
and you can see that I'm
not some kind of wacko.


577
00:59:01.515 --> 00:59:03.212
There is no file on you.

578
00:59:03.256 --> 00:59:05.040
What do you mean
there's no file?


579
00:59:05.084 --> 00:59:08.566
I've never met you before today.

580
00:59:12.265 --> 00:59:14.093
Who are you?

581
00:59:14.136 --> 00:59:15.224
Alex, please.

582
00:59:15.268 --> 00:59:18.097
Look, I would like to...

583
00:59:18.750 --> 00:59:20.621
Suggest...

584
00:59:22.406 --> 00:59:25.147
Alex?

585
00:59:43.862 --> 00:59:47.605
I take it that one's
not worth remembering.


586
00:59:51.652 --> 00:59:53.611
Now you're trespassing.

587
00:59:53.654 --> 00:59:55.047
I know.

588
00:59:55.090 --> 00:59:57.397
I was wondering if you're
ready for that boat ride.


589
00:59:57.441 --> 00:59:59.443
I can't leave Sandra alone.

590
00:59:59.486 --> 01:00:04.622
I have a feeling she
can take care of herself.


591
01:00:05.840 --> 01:00:07.015
I like your necklace.

592
01:00:07.059 --> 01:00:09.757
Thanks.
It belonged to my mother.


593
01:00:09.801 --> 01:00:12.151
Before she died.

594
01:00:15.023 --> 01:00:16.460
It reminds me of her.

595
01:00:16.503 --> 01:00:19.550
Memento Mori.

596
01:00:19.593 --> 01:00:21.203
May I?

597
01:00:21.247 --> 01:00:23.641
Yeah.

598
01:00:23.684 --> 01:00:25.643
She died too soon.

599
01:00:25.686 --> 01:00:28.776
How do you know that?

600
01:00:28.820 --> 01:00:30.517
Because I saw it.

601
01:00:30.561 --> 01:00:33.694
But you can't know that.

602
01:00:33.738 --> 01:00:36.305
Only she can know if
she was ready to die.


603
01:00:36.349 --> 01:00:39.047
Trust me, she wasn't ready.

604
01:00:39.091 --> 01:00:43.443
That may be true,
but it's a very personal thing.


605
01:00:43.487 --> 01:00:48.361
One dies when she wants,
as she wants,


606
01:00:48.405 --> 01:00:49.754
of what she chooses.

607
01:00:49.797 --> 01:00:54.411
My mother chose a man
she thought she could trust.


608
01:00:56.891 --> 01:01:01.069
Memento Mori doesn't mean
to remember the dead, anyway.


609
01:01:01.983 --> 01:01:04.595
What is it, then?

610
01:01:04.638 --> 01:01:10.078
To remember that
we all must die.


611
01:01:12.516 --> 01:01:15.736
I have to get to work.

612
01:01:25.180 --> 01:01:27.356
I know it sounds impossible,

613
01:01:27.400 --> 01:01:31.273
but I know he's here.

614
01:01:31.317 --> 01:01:35.452
Come on, Al,
Louis is dead, remember?


615
01:01:37.628 --> 01:01:39.543
Ok...

616
01:01:39.586 --> 01:01:40.979
Let me put it this way.

617
01:01:41.022 --> 01:01:45.287
If Louis were still
creeping around the house,


618
01:01:45.331 --> 01:01:47.246
which he is not,

619
01:01:47.289 --> 01:01:51.293
but if he were,
and he wanted to get you,


620
01:01:51.337 --> 01:01:54.471
why wouldn't he have
gotten you sooner?


621
01:01:54.514 --> 01:01:57.604
Because that
wouldn't be any fun.


622
01:01:59.214 --> 01:02:02.566
OK, whatever.

623
01:02:02.609 --> 01:02:03.567
I'm out of here.

624
01:02:03.610 --> 01:02:06.395
I'm ready to get
out of here, too.


625
01:02:06.439 --> 01:02:08.615
Excuse me?

626
01:02:08.963 --> 01:02:14.882
I said I want to leave
and not come back.


627
01:02:18.582 --> 01:02:20.018
That's great.
That's great.


628
01:02:20.061 --> 01:02:24.544
I think there's
hope for you yet.


629
01:02:24.588 --> 01:02:26.633
I got to go.

630
01:02:27.808 --> 01:02:29.549
Wait...

631
01:02:29.593 --> 01:02:31.551
What?

632
01:02:31.595 --> 01:02:33.553
Take this with you.

633
01:02:33.597 --> 01:02:34.685
Thank you very much.

634
01:02:34.728 --> 01:02:36.904
You're going out like that?

635
01:02:36.948 --> 01:02:38.906
Yes, I'm going out like this.

636
01:02:40.473 --> 01:02:41.909
What?

637
01:02:41.953 --> 01:02:45.783
I said I'll be fine.
Try not to worry about me so much.


638
01:02:45.826 --> 01:02:47.611
It's supposed to rain later,
and...


639
01:02:47.654 --> 01:02:48.568
Alex...

640
01:02:48.612 --> 01:02:53.094
I'll be fine.

641
01:04:02.424 --> 01:04:05.384
Hello?

642
01:04:32.846 --> 01:04:35.632
Sandra?

643
01:04:48.601 --> 01:04:50.385
Sandra!

644
01:06:06.940 --> 01:06:09.377
Sorry, miss, we're not open yet.

645
01:06:09.421 --> 01:06:13.425
Oh, Alex, hi!
I didn't see it was you.


646
01:06:13.468 --> 01:06:16.167
Come on, don't
look so surprised.


647
01:06:16.210 --> 01:06:20.475
I told you I never hold a
grudge once I get even.


648
01:06:20.519 --> 01:06:21.563
You know...

649
01:06:21.607 --> 01:06:24.566
I think I've figured out
your problem.


650
01:06:24.610 --> 01:06:27.744
Well, one of your problems.

651
01:06:28.745 --> 01:06:31.443
You don't know how
to have any fun.


652
01:06:31.486 --> 01:06:34.663
See, aren't you glad we met?

653
01:06:34.707 --> 01:06:37.449
I curse the day
you ever found me.


654
01:06:38.537 --> 01:06:42.149
Am I bleeding?
I think I've been cut.


655
01:06:42.193 --> 01:06:45.500
You've still got it wrong, Alex.

656
01:06:45.544 --> 01:06:48.634
I didn't find you.

657
01:06:49.853 --> 01:06:52.377
You found me.

658
01:06:52.420 --> 01:06:55.249
You can find me again, Alex.

659
01:06:55.293 --> 01:06:59.079
You've always known
where to find me.


660
01:06:59.123 --> 01:07:00.689
No!

661
01:08:25.296 --> 01:08:27.602
I'll take you.

662
01:08:51.409 --> 01:08:53.933
I feel like I'm going to hell.

663
01:08:53.977 --> 01:08:59.765
Sometimes you have to face your
demons in order to see the angels, Alex.


664
01:09:10.950 --> 01:09:14.823
It's time to let go.

665
01:09:14.867 --> 01:09:16.869
I can't.

666
01:09:18.915 --> 01:09:20.960
I haven't lived yet.

667
01:09:21.004 --> 01:09:24.137
Then why are you here?

668
01:10:55.402 --> 01:10:57.578
Michael.

669
01:12:53.172 --> 01:12:56.654
I'm late. I'm late
for a very important date.


670
01:12:57.524 --> 01:12:59.526
Watch where you're going.

671
01:13:12.583 --> 01:13:17.109
I told you to watch
where you're going.


672
01:13:43.135 --> 01:13:45.137
Gotcha!

673
01:16:25.210 --> 01:16:26.646
Help me, Alex!

674
01:16:26.690 --> 01:16:30.041
Please don't leave me here.

675
01:16:30.084 --> 01:16:33.000
Don't leave me alone with him.

676
01:16:33.044 --> 01:16:34.132
Please!

677
01:16:34.175 --> 01:16:37.353
It's you he wants!

678
01:17:07.383 --> 01:17:10.951
Nice of you to join us, Alex.

679
01:17:32.582 --> 01:17:33.974
Remember this?

680
01:17:34.018 --> 01:17:37.151
This is my favorite part.

681
01:17:38.504 --> 01:17:40.464
Shame you caught me
and your mother doing it, too.


682
01:17:40.489 --> 01:17:41.895
Might not have had to kill her.

683
01:17:41.939 --> 01:17:43.288
You would have anyway.

684
01:17:43.331 --> 01:17:45.943
She knew you could only
get it up with little girls.


685
01:17:45.986 --> 01:17:48.206
You know, guilt is
a funny thing, Alex.


686
01:17:48.249 --> 01:17:50.469
It haunts you
as real as any ghost.


687
01:17:51.731 --> 01:17:52.794
I think you're just
too scared to admit it.


688
01:17:52.819 --> 01:17:54.342
Which is fine
with us, by the way,


689
01:17:54.386 --> 01:17:55.953
because the longer you hang on,

690
01:17:55.996 --> 01:17:59.435
the longer we get to play.

691
01:18:00.000 --> 01:18:05.266
I'm just hanging on long enough
to blow your fucking head off.


692
01:18:05.310 --> 01:18:07.617
Don't be hasty.

693
01:18:07.660 --> 01:18:10.271
You wouldn't hurt
a clown, would you?


694
01:18:13.492 --> 01:18:15.799
Will I?
Won't I?


695
01:18:15.842 --> 01:18:16.930
You don't have the guts.

696
01:18:16.974 --> 01:18:20.499
Will I?
Won't I?


697
01:18:20.543 --> 01:18:24.808
Won't I join the dance?

698
01:19:28.480 --> 01:19:31.396
Come on, Sandra!

699
01:20:02.122 --> 01:20:07.954
Sometimes bad memories have
a way of following you around.


700
01:20:12.611 --> 01:20:18.138
I said I'll be fine.
Quit worrying about me so much.


701
01:20:24.667 --> 01:20:27.495
You're not afraid, are you?

702
01:20:31.021 --> 01:20:35.025
Sid, voice-over: I KNOW
YOU'VE BEEN HAVING A HARD TIME.


703
01:20:35.068 --> 01:20:37.767
It's going to be OK, though.

704
01:20:37.810 --> 01:20:39.986
I hope you know that.

705
01:21:52.015 --> 01:21:53.843
Al?

706
01:21:56.019 --> 01:21:57.934
Alex?

707
01:22:01.067 --> 01:22:03.156
That looks like your car.

708
01:22:07.073 --> 01:22:08.771
Ain't this where they
had that carnival?


709
01:22:08.814 --> 01:22:14.254
Carnival? Hasn't been a
carnival out here in 20 years.


710
01:22:46.460 --> 01:22:51.161
Did you notice any strange behavior?
Mood swings?


711
01:22:51.204 --> 01:22:54.599
When was the last
time you saw her?


712
01:22:56.514 --> 01:22:58.516
Excuse me.

713
01:23:48.827 --> 01:23:50.916
Hello.

714
01:23:55.703 --> 01:23:57.314
Hello?